  - id: b-ml5fqzza-huosjv
    scope: global
    category: architecture
    content: "Button pattern in Lua UI DSL: Use `dsl.button({ text, buttonCallback,
      style })` for interactive buttons. The buttonCallback receives the button
      context and handles click events. For text-based clickable elements, use
      `dsl.text()` with `onClick` property and `gui.set_enabled(node, true)` to
      enable input. Button state can be managed by storing node references and
      updating via `gui.set_text()` or `gui.set_color()`."
    source: learned
